The paper deals with mathematical methods for pairwise comparisons, which are commonly used in decision-making and optimization problems. The focus is on the orthogonalization process, which is a fundamental concept in linear algebra and has applications in various fields of computer science. Therefore, cs.MS (Mathematical Software) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the properties of consistent approximations, which are relevant to cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-categories. The method of deriving a priority vector is related to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) sub-categories.
